The paper deals with clustering of multi-view data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The proposed method involves the use of Markov chains and structured sparsity-inducing norms to handle errors in the data. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
